review_blob: This is not one of Tired Hands best. It is described as a spiced Saison. It has an off taste and a sour finish. Not sure if the sour was intended. It has significant hops, with simcoe hops dominating. Brewery is still one of the best around.
Very nice, heady IPA. Citrus notes, not overly choppy. Aroma is good, appearance is cloudy, pale orange. Brought home a growler.... mmm...
